With meshes so far there is a big problem: the quality of reconstruction is not great. Geometry topology usually terrible as most projects use simple marching cubes algorithms for approximating Gaussian Splatts surface. Another problem with marching cubes is highly noisy surfaces. There are some methods that are capable of extracting relatively decent meshes, i.e. SUGAR (https://github.com/Anttwo/SuGaR)  but they are not very fast all in all. There are similar problems with neural radiansce fields, although there are more methods for reconstructing geometry from them. For example, using signed distance fields (e.g. https://arxiv.org/html/2403.19985v1) conversion and similar.
